article.headline: S. Dakota St. 74, S. Utah 69
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Garrett Callahan scored 24 points and Anthony Cordova added 16 to lead South Dakota State to a 74-69 win over Southern Utah Thursday in the Summit League. Callahan had two 3-pointers and went 5-for-7 from the field. He was 12-for-12 from the free throw line, helping the Jackrabbits (11-15, 6-8) finish the night 20 of 25. SDSU's Kai Williams had 10 points and eight rebounds. Southern Utah (8-16, 6-7) outshot SDSU from the field and from 3-point range and outrebounded the Jackrabbits 30-28. But it was just 11 of 14 from the line. Davis Baker had 26 points and four assists for the Thunderbirds. Tyler Quinney added 10 points.
